<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-41-0999 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book covers comprehensively the subject of coal preparation technology.The first 12 chapters (volume 1) cover the elements of coal use, properties,size reduction, sizing, concentration, dewatering and process-evaluationtechniques. Volume 2 introduces a variety of specialized topics whichinclude: instrumentation and control; materials handling; blending andhomogenization; plant design; testing of coal for the market; economicsof coal preparation; waste disposal and environmental factors; computerapplications; plant performance testing; coal sampling; and specializedfine-coal beneficiation methods.</TEXT></DOC>